parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to safety risks, especially when driving on the road.
symptoms: Key gets stuck in the ignition
key will not turn to the off position
key will not come out of the ignition switch
car has to be stalled manually to stop running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, such as stalling, loss of power, and malfunctioning of critical systems like airbags and brakes.
The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
The failure of the brake system can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brake pads and rotors need to be replaced frequently

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to safety risks.
The failure of the door latch can cause the door to open while driving, leading to safety risks.
symptoms: Door does not close and latch correctly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HPFP can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The glow plug light may flash
the "Service Engine Now" indicator may light
and the vehicle may stall or die.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine may stall or die
and the fuel system may be contaminated with metal shavings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine may stall or die
and the glow plug light may flash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or jerk, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates while accelerating

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to stall or jerk, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
or does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window and speaker system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The power window does not work properly
and the speakers malfunction or produce a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or loss of control.
The failure of the emissions system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake and transmission can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The parking brake does not engage properly
and the transmission may slip or hesitate.
